# Gradle Guidelines

globs: ["**/*.gradle.kts", "**/libs.versions.toml"]

## Version Catalog
All dependencies and versions are managed in `gradle/libs.versions.toml`.

When adding new dependencies:
1. Add version to `[versions]` section
2. Add library to `[libraries]` section
3. Add plugins to `[plugins]` section
4. Reference using `libs.` in build.gradle.kts files

## Common Tasks
Prefer using `just` commands which wrap Gradle:
- `just build` - Build all platforms
- `just build-shared` - Build only shared module
- `just build-android` - Build Android app
- `just clean` - Clean build outputs

Direct Gradle commands (for reference):
- `./gradlew build` - Full build
- `./gradlew :shared:build` - Build only shared module
- `./gradlew :android:assembleDebug` - Build Android debug APK

## Plugin Configuration
Plugins are applied via version catalog aliases. Check `gradle/libs.versions.toml` for available plugins.
